  univ ∈ T ∧
  (∀ s t, s ∈ T → t ∈ T → s ∩ t ∈ T) ∧
  (∀s, (∀t ∈ s, t ∈ T) → sUnion s ∈ T)

records.nl_statement: Suppose $T \in \mathcal{L}(V)$ is such that every vector in $V$ is an eigenvector of $T$. Prove that $T$ is a scalar multiple of the identity operator.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Fintype Complex Polynomial LinearMap FiniteDimensional Module Module.End
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_5_12 {F V : Type*} [AddCommGroup V] [Field F]
  [Module F V] {S : End F V}
  (hS : ∀ v : V, ∃ c : F, v ∈ eigenspace S c) :
  ∃ c : F, S = c • LinearMap.id :=
